        <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
            <head>Biographical/Historical Information </head>
            <p>John Bankhead Magruder (May 1, 1807 â€“ February 19, 1871), a native of Port Royal, VA,
                submitted this requisition during his time as a general for the Confederate Army.
                Magruder had previously served in the US Army, and would later serve with the
                Imperial Mexican Army. He is known for his efforts in the 1862 Peninsula Campaign
                and in successfully defending Galveston, Texas, against the Union Army and Navy
                early in 1863. </p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
            <head>Scope and Content </head>
            <p>Special requisition No. 40 for steel pens, inkstands, envelopes, papers and wafers
                for the use of Magruder and his staff. Materials issued by R{obert} J. Morrison at
                Williamsburg, {Va.} on 10 July 1861. Printed form with manuscript insertions. </p>
        </scopecontent>
